### Description

Component provides an injectable "Foobar" but the component is unable to inject an InjectionToken which itself is trying to inject "Foobar".

```ts
@Injectable()
class Foobar {}

const FOOBAR = new InjectionToken('Foobar', {
  factory: () => {
    return inject(Foobar); // This throws an error that Foobar is not found
  },
  providedIn: null, // The docs suggest this is the same as undefined, and should use the local injector
});

@Component({
  selector: 'my-app',
  template: 'Hello',
  providers: [Foobar],
})
export class AppComponent {
  constructor(@Inject(FOOBAR) foobar: Foobar) {
    console.log(foobar);
  }
}
```

I would expect `inject(Foobar)` within the InjectionToken to return the local Foobar provided in this component.

